AGI -&nbsp; There is a date, among many, where Matteo Zuppi became a popular face. The <a href="https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/2022-01-14/funerali-state-sassoli-addio-15235501/">day of the funeral of the President of the European Parliament,</a> David Sassoli in Rome, in which the Cardinal of Bologna was called to celebrate the function and remember the friend who died at 65 years for a lucimia. In those days of deep mourning, in Rome, they noticed all, of every political side, starting from President Sergio Mattarella, then Premier Mario Draghi, Giorgia Meloni and Matteo Salvini, the European authorities like Roberta Metsola, and the journalists of the Tg1 for a burning room that in Campidoglio did not know rest, which had turned into a choral embrace of all those worlds that crossed. &nbsp;
In one of the last messages to his wife Alessandra Vittorini said: "I've had a very beautiful life, although a little complicated, and ending it at 65 years is really too early." &nbsp;
It was on January 14, 2022, when Zuppi today among the "papals", schoolmate of Sassoli and Alessandra, "presented" to the general public in the church of Santa Maria degli Angeli in Rome, in front of major European authorities.&nbsp;
Here an extract of the homily that pronounced that day: "We cling to Alessandra, who with David walked hand in hand from school benches,» Livia and Giulio, his brothers and sisters and the many who considered him “one of us”, almost instinctively, for that air devoid of supponence, of alternation, empathic, in short, a little for all a classmate! David helps us to look at the sky - sometimes so great to scare, that puts the dizziness - he who always sought it, as a Christian in search yet convinced, that he breathed the faith and the democratic and civil Catholic commitment at home, with the many friends of his father and then his, impetuous believers and fans like Giorgio La Pira or Mazzolari, like Davide Maria Turoldo, of which bears the name".
"Credent serene but without avoiding difficult doubts and questions, confident in God's love, the root of his commitment, always shared with someone, as it must be, because the Christian as every man is not an island, but always has a community with which to live the commandment of love one another: Scouts, the White Rose group with Paolo Giuntella (Sophie and Hans Scholl, the leaders of the Weiss Rose were for him the stars of the morning of Europe, killed by the Nazis for their freedom, so that when he was elected honored as a debt to them by placing a huge white rose on a European background in parliament because &nbsp; "our story is written in their desire for freedom"). With so many he shared his I Care, – I think, for example, the Church of Rome of February 74 and Fr. Luigi Di Liegro – always combining personal faith and commitment in history, starting from the last, from the victims who “have the eyes all the same”, full of respect and grace as his character. There are those who say that the Christian is a gentleman precisely because Christian, although no lieutenant, because he has a treasure of love that makes him such. A poor man who makes others rich."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The Gospel tells us about Beatitude. Attention, it is not different from human happiness, indeed it is just full happiness, just what we all seek. The bliss of the Gospel is not an ultimate reward for some sacrifice, but freedom from the infinite pornographic caricatures of happiness of individual well-being at any price. There is no joy alone! The joy of the Gospel unites, does not divide from others and we seek not a joy of happening, but true and lasting. - he had said Zuppi -&nbsp;I must say that seeing how much love has straited in these days around David and his family I understand with greater clarity that joy > comes from what is given to others and that then, only after giving it, you receive, always, because joy is in being and not in having, in thinking for and not in seeking your own interest. Happy are the poor in spirit, who does not know everything alone, who indeed knows that it is not rich and does not pretend to be so much as not to apologize or help, who learns and seeks. Blessed are the afflicted: not those who seek suffering, but those who do not escape from difficulties, face them for love and for love weeps for the beloved. Blessed are the myths, who does not seek in the other the pity but the gift that is, who does not respond to evil with evil, who in a loving way tries to do to others what he wants is done to him".
"Di David I believe that we all bring his smile into our hearts, which is the first way to welcome and respect the other >, without satisfaction, simply. Someone said he never saw anyone angry with David! &nbsp;Beati are those who are hungry and thirsty for justice, who cannot be well if someone next to him suffers, who do not change channel or pretend not to see or that does not concern them if there is a person in danger in the middle of the sea or the cold on the doorstep. They are hungry for justice because they do not get used to injustice and remember that the justice of God is to take care of the younger brothers of Jesus and that the suffering of the other is mine. Blessed are the merciful, who judges but always for love, who seeks the hidden good, who thinks that there is always hope, who chooses to console rather than make suffer.> Blessed are the pure ones of heart, those who see without malice, not because naive but because they see well, deep, free from calculations, from conveniences, disinterested because they have a greater interest, those who do not have prejudices when facing a discussion, who are not afraid to understand the position of the other, even if distant from him, who do not cry but listen knowing that there is always something to learn. Blessed are the operators of peace, > the artisans, that they do not give up to “make peace” starting from the small and possible gestures of care, dirtying their hands with life, with the contradictions of the neighbor, with the effort to tighten that of the enemy that if you do it will turn into brother. Blessed are the persecuted because of justice, not the one that divides with coldness the cake in part equal even if the one who has to eat it is not equal, as strictly unveiled a just like Don Milani > because to love everyone you start from the many, (quanti!) Gianni who have no chance. God proclaiming the bliss seems to tell us that everyone has the right to happiness and that he wants and that this does not end. Let us wonder what we have to give to others so that they are happy, because mine is theirs. It is true, as someone has said wisely, that we must always see life with the eyes of others. That's why we thank the Lord for David."
"He was blessed also in the affliction, during his illness > which he welcomed with dignity, without weighing, spending until the end, inviting everyone to look away, living with the strength of his ideals and love that so surrounded and accompanied him. For a believer bliss is to obey his own conscience and purify the intentions on which the other choices depend. Here, the full bliss that David lives today and with his life reminds us and gives us. David was a separate man, but of all, because his part was that of the person. For this reason politics was, it had to be for the common good > and democracy always inclusive, humanitarian and humanist. That is why he wanted united Europe and with the founding values, which served so that his institutions worked, that he loved because son of the generation who had seen the war and horrors of the genocide and the Nazi and fascist pagan violence, of the many nationalisms, son of resistance and its values, those on which our Republic is founded and which inspired our founding fathers. It is from that immanent suffering – that for which he wanted the President to go to Fossoli, one of the many places of suffering of the barbarism of war – that was born his commitment. Not ideologies, but ideals; not calculations, but a vision because also Europe cannot live for itself, because Christianity is not an idea, but a person, Jesus, who passes through people and in history."
