"I make my last greeting for last Christmas, already very sick, today that he is born to the life of heaven. “In this year we listened to the silence of the planet and we were afraid but we reacted and built a new solidarity because no one is safe alone. We have seen new walls, our boundaries > in some cases have become boundaries between moral and immoral, > between humanity and humanity. Erect walls against people seeking shelter from cold, hunger, war and poverty. We have finally realized after years of cruel rigorism that inequality is no longer tolerable or acceptable, than living in precariousness is not human, that poverty is a reality that should not be hidden but that must be fought and defeated. The duty of the European institutions: protect the weakest and not ask for other sacrifices by adding pain.> Merry Christmas..The period of Christmas is the period of birth of hope and hope we are when we do not close our eyes before those who need it, when we do not raise walls to our borders, when we fight against all injustices. Greetings to us, best wishes to our hope.” Thank you, man of hope for all. David Maria Turoldo wrote a poem that David knew in memory: “God of life, you are born, who continues to be born in every life. He's calling for dead now, because he doesn't die, nobody dies. nothing and no one: nothing and no one dies because You are. You are and everything lives, it is all in you that lives: even death!"
